# Automatically downloads compromised ua-parser-js@0.7.29
# Malicious postinstall script executes:
# - Steals credentials from environment variables
# - Installs cryptocurrency miner
# - Exfiltrates SSH keys and .npmrc tokens
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Using `*`, `latest`, or wide version ranges allows automatic installation of compromised versions
- No package-lock.json means different versions on each install
- No integrity verification - packages aren't verified against known hashes
- postinstall scripts execute arbitrary code during installation
- No audit or vulnerability scanning in CI/CD

