**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Go's default proxy (proxy.golang.org) is checked before private sources
- No GOPRIVATE environment variable restricts module resolution
- Attackers can register packages using your company's namespace on public proxies
- Malicious init() functions execute during import, before any code review
- CI/CD systems with broad network access become attack pivot points

